Mark arrived late to the station. He should have left earlier, but he got distracted. If he could have caught the earlier bus, he would have been on time. Now, he regrets not checking the schedule more carefully. He could have avoided this whole situation. Next time, he should have a better plan. He really would have preferred to be on that train.
